  "prompt": "Is the past tense of \"troubleshoot\" troubleshooted or troubleshot? Why?",
  "response": "The correct past tense of \"troubleshoot\" is \"troubleshot.\" This irregular form follows the pattern of other compound verbs that end with \"shoot,\" like \"overshoot\" (overshot) and \"undershoot\" (undershot). The irregular past tense retains the unique transformation that \"shoot\" undergoes when converting to past tense. Using \"troubleshot\" aligns with standard grammatical conventions, even though \"troubleshooted\" is sometimes informally used.",
